import org.apache.zeppelin.display.angular.paragraphscope._
import AngularElem._
import org.apache.spark.storage.StorageLevel
import scala.util.matching.Regex

// Define constants  
val tbl = "opennantes"

val prefixes = Map( "^<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" -> "<rdf_",
                    "^<http://www.w3.org/2006/vcard/ns#" -> "<vcard_",
                    "^<http://schema.org/" -> "<sch_",
                    "^<http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml/microdata#" -> "<md_",
                    "^<http://data-vocabulary.org/" -> "<dv_",
                    "^<http://purl.org/dc/terms" -> "<dct_")

def prefixIt(s:String) : String = {
    var res = s
    for ((k,v) <- prefixes)
        res = res.replaceFirst(k,v)
    
    return res.replaceFirst(">$","").replaceFirst("^<","").replaceAll("/","_")
}

// declare functin for sql engine 
sqlContext.udf.register("prefixIt", (s: String) => prefixIt(s))

// Load blacklist and whitelist of url 
spark.read.option("header","true").csv("whitelist.csv").createOrReplaceTempView("whitelist")
spark.read.option("header","true").csv("blacklist.csv").createOrReplaceTempView("blacklist")


val data = spark
    //.read.textFile("ofInterest.gz/*.txt")
    .sql("SELECT graph, subject, prefixIt(predicate) as predicate, object FROM "+tbl)
    //.read.parquet("open-data-plus/results/oneOfEach")
    .filter("graph IS NOT NULL")
    //.filter("graph NOT IN  (SELECT DISTINCT url FROM whitelist) ")
    //.filter("graph NOT IN  (SELECT DISTINCT url FROM blacklist) ")
    //.persist(StorageLevel.MEMORY_AND_DISK)
    
data.show
data.createOrReplaceTempView("data")

val dataContent = data.where("predicate <> 'rdf_type'  AND  predicate <> 'md_item'").cache
dataContent.createOrReplaceTempView("dataContent")

val dataTypes = data.where("""  
        predicate = 'rdf_type' 
    OR  predicate = 'md_item' """).cache
dataTypes.createOrReplaceTempView("dataTypes")                        

val rdfType = dataTypes.filter("predicate = 'rdf_type'").cache
val microdata = dataTypes.filter("predicate = 'md_item'").cache

val leaf = dataContent.filter("object NOT LIKE '_:%'").cache
val bn = dataContent.filter("object LIKE '_:%'").cache

paragraphs.title: Nantes
paragraphs.text:
%angular

Finding Nantes

We look for predicate that describes Nantes with as much uniqness as possible

Basic filtering

Applied to the whole data in a single read. We search for a few post code matching the city and the city name inside the NQuads. We filter the search on some very specific predicate.

Sibligns node

Here comes the issue, to find any form of neighbourhood we need to join the data to the original dataset. if its a small set then we can broadcast but here is the general method.

Parent / children

Capturing the parent node enable a second row much faster. Same for eventual children

Graph and Subject

import spark.implicits._

var nantes = leaf.where("""
        (   
            predicate LIKE '%post%ode%'
            AND 
            object LIKE '%44%'
            )
        OR(
               (predicate LIKE '%ocality%'
                OR
                predicate LIKE '%address%'
                OR
                predicate LIKE '%title%')
            AND
            object LIKE '%Nantes%')
    """).as('nantes).dropDuplicates.cache
nantes.createOrReplaceTempView("nantes")
nantes.show
    
// TODO make the join take into account URL 
var hop1 = nantes.join(data.as('d), $"nantes.graph" === $"d.graph" && 
    ($"nantes.subject" === $"d.subject" || $"nantes.subject" === $"d.object" || $"nantes.object" === $"d.subject"))
                .select("d.graph","d.subject", "d.predicate", "d.object")
                .dropDuplicates
                .cache
            
hop1.show
hop1.createOrReplaceTempView("hop1")


var hop2 = hop1.as('hop1)
    .join(data.as('d2),  $"hop1.graph" === $"d2.graph"  &&
      ($"hop1.subject" === $"d2.subject" || $"hop1.subject" === $"d2.object" || $"hop1.object" === $"d2.subject"))
    .select("d2.graph","d2.subject", "d2.predicate", "d2.object")
    .dropDuplicates
    .cache
                
hop2.show                
hop2.createOrReplaceTempView("hop2")

var hop3 = hop2.as('hop2)
    .join(data.as('d),  $"hop2.graph" === $"d.graph"  &&
      ($"hop2.subject" === $"d.subject" || $"hop2.subject" === $"d.object" || $"hop2.object" === $"d.subject"))
    .select("d.graph","d.subject", "d.predicate", "d.object")
    .dropDuplicates
    .cache
                
hop3.show                
hop3.createOrReplaceTempView("hop3")
 
var addressCard = nantes
    .join(data.as('d), $"nantes.graph" === $"d.graph" && $"nantes.subject" === $"d.subject")
    .select("d.graph","d.subject","d.predicate","d.object")

    .agg(first("object"))
    .cache

import spark.implicits._

val preds = dataTypes.select(col("graph").as("g"),col("subject").as("s"),col("object").as("type"))
preds.select("type", "s").show(false)
    
val join = preds.join(dataContent, dataContent("graph") === preds("g") && dataContent("subject") === preds("s"), "right")
join.show

val schemas = join.select("type","predicate")
    .where("type LIKE '<%>' AND predicate LIKE '<%>' ")
    .groupBy("type","predicate")
    .pivot("type")
    .agg(count("predicate"));

schemas.show
schemas.write
    .mode("overwrite")
    .saveAsTable("schemas")
